.TH SIMPLE_SHELL 1 "December 2025" "Holberton School" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
simple_shell \- a simple UNIX command interpreter

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hsh

.SH DESCRIPTION
Simple Shell is a basic command-line interpreter written in C.
It reads commands from standard input and executes them.

The shell works in both interactive and non-interactive modes.

.SH INVOCATION
Interactive mode:
.RS
./hsh
.RE

Non-interactive mode:
.RS
echo "ls -l" | ./hsh
.RE

.SH BUILT-IN COMMANDS
.TP
.B exit
Exit the shell.

.TP
.B env
Print the current environment variables.

.SH FEATURES
- Executes commands found in the PATH
- Handles command arguments
- Handles EOF (Ctrl+D)
- Error handling for invalid commands

.SH RETURN VALUE
Returns 0 on success, and non-zero on error.

.SH AUTHOR
Written by Holberton School students.

.SH SEE ALSO
sh(1), bash(1)
